  "prompt": "How do I print an application form on the OJAS website?",
  "response": "To print an application form on the OJAS (Online Job Application System) website, typically follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the official OJAS website (usually ojas.gujarat.gov.in)\n\n2. Log in to your account using your registration details\n\n3. Find the specific job application you want to print\n\n4. Look for an option like \"Print Application Form\" or \"Download Application\"\n\n5. Click on the print/download button\n\n6. The application form will open as a PDF\n\n7. Use your browser's print function (Ctrl+P or File > Print) to print the form\n\nNote: The exact steps might vary slightly depending on the specific job application and current website design. If you're having trouble, you can:\n- Check the website's help/FAQ section\n- Contact OJAS customer support\n- Ensure you have a PDF reader installed\n\nWould you like me to provide more specific guidance about a particular application?",
